The food reminds me of family gatherings. Some places you will go and accept that it is "Jamacian" food. At Mama's it is JAMACIAN FOOD. The portions are generous for NY takeout and the food tastes completely authentic, because it is. I can come for the lunch special or dinner and be full and satisfied, often with leftovers for later.  I have had the Ackee and Saltfish early in the morning, Jerk Chicken for Lunch many times and Oxtail at dinner. All five stars  Extremely glad that they have not closed thier doors in these hard times. Keep it up!

As a loyal customer for three years I can say Mama’s is probably the best Jamaican restaurant in Harlem. I usually get oxtail or jerk salmon, with rice and peas. They give a generous amount of oxtail gravy if you ask (which is unheard of in most Jamaican restaurants). Gravy is always think and dark like it should be and not runny or too oily. But I will say the rice has UNDERCOOKED the last few times I’ve been there. If you want oxtail you should arrive before 7 pm because that’s when they usually run out, on the weekends at least.

If you're looking for great Jamaican food that Caribbean Flavor that you had when you took that trip to Montego Bay, then this is the spot for you. This location does have a little counter area for you to sit and enjoy a quick meal but this is more of a takeout to go place but the food is definitely worth it We came on a Friday afternoon about 1pm the counter staff was so polite and helpful, didn't rush you to order, even went the extra mile to wrap my to go order when I needed it.  All the way from Dallas-Fort Worth Texas, we were in the city for a day trip taking care of some travel documents when we came across Mama's. This spot was definitely worth it, my wife myself and my son ordered stew chicken rice and peas oxtails rice and peas mac and cheese sat down ate and enjoyed. The food was so good we ordered to go had to catch a flight in 2 hours we ordered curry goat meal, jerk chicken meal, two beef patties two Coco bread and we were good to go. The young lady at the counter made sure to wrap my orders real good in order for me not to have any issues with TSA. Normally we don't like carrying food across the airport on a plane to any distance but mama's are so good we had to take some back to Texas. Mama's was definitely a good hidden spot in my old hometown. Even though we now live in Dallas-Fort Worth New York City is still in the heart and food like this always makes it worth the trip to come back home.  And I'm still a New York Giants fan my man Eli still has another Superbowl left in him. Food made it to Fort Worth safely can't wait to dig in.
